==Coat of arms== [[File:CAO district of Moscow coa.png|thumb|Coat of arms of Central Administrative Okrug]]
The [[Kremlin Hill]], from which the colonization of Moscow began, is depicted under Yury Dolgoruky. The purple background symbolizes the supreme power of Russia, concentrated in Central Administrative Okrug. The gold [[unicorn]] was a traditional symbol of the Russian [[Tsar]]s. Below him an ancient [[Kremlin]] white-stone wall is featured.
