'''Eduardo Menichetti Pilas''' (1950/51 &ndash; 8 July 2007) was a [[Chile]]an businessman from [[Santiago]], best known as the president of the football club [[Colo-Colo]] from 1990 to 1995. During his five-year tenure, the club won three [[Campeonato Nacional (Chile)|Campeonato Nacional]] titles and three international titles.
Menichetti died from [[colorectal cancer]] on 8 July 2007 at the age of 56. He was survived by his two children.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/2007/07/08/261926/eduardo-menichetti-fallecio-a-los-56-anos.html|title=Eduardo Menichetti falleció a los 56 años|work=[[El Mercurio]]|date=8 July 2007|accessdate=21 September 2015|language=Spanish}}</ref>
